Group 9 - CSE 545
Note About User Roles and Departments:
In this setup, roles and departments are joined to users via a many
to many relationship. As such, there is a "roles_users" table and a
"departments_users" table. Each table maintains entries that link
users to their departments and roles. This way, a user can be part
of more than one department or role. This implementation allows
for expansion later on in case business requirement change. For
our purposes, the Roles table will contain Employee, Manager,
Corporate, and Administrator. The Departments table will contain
Human Resources, IT Support, Logistics and Supply, Research
and Development, and Sales
